Watson’s Record 15 Sixes Leads Australia to 9 Wicket Win Over Bangladesh

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-04-11T10:27:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/watson-s-record-15-sixes-leads-australia-to-9-wicket-win-over-bangladesh.html
Shane Watson  scored 185 runs from
96 balls, including a record 15 sixes, while leading Australia
to a nine-wicket victory over Bangladesh in their second one-day
cricket International in Mirpur.  Watson, also set a mark for most runs from boundaries in a
one-day match, combined for 170 runs with  Ricky Ponting , who
ended on 37. Australia reached 232-1 with 144 balls remaining.
Opener Brad Haddin added 8 before being caught by Mahmudallah.  Bangladesh won the toss, and elected to bat, reaching 229-7
in their 50 overs. The opening batsmen, Tamim Iqbal and Imrul
Kayes, each were out for 5, caught by Watson. Mushfiqur Rahim
was 81 not out, with Shahriar Nafees adding 56 for the home side
before being caught and bowled by  Steven Smith , who ended up
2-34. Shafiul Islam was not out on 9 at the end of the innings.  Mitchell Johnson was 3-54 for Australia. The visitors took
the three-match series after winning the first one-day by 60
runs. It’s the first series where Australia has been led by
 Michael Clarke , who replaced Ricky Ponting as captain after the
World Cup. The final match is in Dhaka in two days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  